title: Show HN: Discover the mafias of top tech companies
text:
I created a one page site to browse the 'mafias' of top tech companies. I was surprised to find this didn't really exist anywhere.

For now it just shows Paypal, HubSpot, and Stripe, but may add others if theres interest. This was a chance for me to play with a few tools like Formspark, Netlify, ExactBuyer, and React.

I was inspired by similar sites like layoffs.fyi that are very simple, but valuable data using Airtable embeds.

Ask HN: Why not have a lecture note taking app that knows what you will write?
text:
In particular, the app could get the lecture notes in advance and then use them to autocorrect and autocomplete the student's notes during the lecture as they make them in real-time.

The student could even take rough notes with a pen and have the app automatically convert them into LaTeX in a way that preserves some of the student's formatting and is 100% accurate with respect to the professor's lecture notes.
